## Lore Goblin — Spec Kit Context

**Constitution**: `.specify/memory/constitution.md` (v1.0.0)

### Non-Negotiable Principles

- **Local-first**: Docker Compose, SQLite, Ollama-compatible models; cloud not required for core use
- **Source-grounded**: Answer only from saved campaign sources; cite or admit unknown
- **Provenance**: Preserve who submitted each note; never silently merge conflicting accounts
- **Discord-first**: Player UX via slash commands; web UI for setup, guild linking, tone config
- **Campaign tone**: Configurable per campaign; personality MUST NOT override correctness or citations
- **Simplicity**: Three-app layout (`apps/api`, `apps/web`, `apps/discord-bot`); YAGNI
- **Test-first**: Tests written and failing before implementation (TDD, non-negotiable)

### Repository Layout

```text
apps/api/          FastAPI backend, SQLite, retrieval, Ollama adapter
apps/web/          React + TypeScript setup and chat UI
apps/discord-bot/  Discord slash command client
specs/             Feature specs (###-feature-name/)
```

### Workflow

New features follow spec-kit: `/speckit-specify` → `/speckit-plan` → `/speckit-tasks` → `/speckit-implement`.

Plans MUST include Constitution Check gates (see `.specify/templates/plan-template.md`).

For the active feature's technical details, read the current plan at `specs/002-player-characters/plan.md`.
